-- DriverWorkitems / TernaryBuildZ3 isolation — the ternary null-operand
-- regression (sample-ternary-crash-diagnosis.md). A branch sub-expression
-- that never pushed a Z3 AST leaves handle 0; the OLD code passed 0
-- straight to Z3_mk_ite, which derefs null and SIGSEGVs (exit 139). The
-- guard must instead halt NAMEABLY: a 0 operand ⇒ Exit(7). Feeds a null
-- `then_h` and asserts the kernel exits 7 cleanly.
--
-- entry: main
-- expect: exit = 7
import "stdlib/kernel.ev"
import "compiler2/translate2_bool.ev"

claim main
    e_ite ∈ Effect
    TernaryBuildZ3(ctx_h ↦ 1, cond_h ↦ 99, then_h ↦ 0, else_h ↦ 42, prescan ↦ false, eff ↦ e_ite)
    effects ∈ Seq(Effect) = ⟨e_ite⟩
